Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 
degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with #aluminum foil{}. Trim, then thinly slice 
@scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Trim and peel @carrots{4}, then 
slice diagonally into ½-inch-thick pieces. Core and finely chop 
@roma tomatoes{2}(finely chopped). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Cut 
@yukon gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough water to cover by 2 inches. Cover 
and bring to a boil. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup cooking 
water, then drain. Return empty #pot{} to stove. Heat a drizzle of 
@vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in same pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion 
whites and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Remove pot from heat and add potatoes, @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @butter{2%tablespoon}, 
¼ cup cooking water, and a few big pinches of @salt{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} 
to desired consistency, adding more cooking water if necessary. Meanwhile, in a 
#small bowl{}, whisk half the @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (we'll use the rest in 
step 5), @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} until 
smooth.

Toss carrots and dressing on lined baking sheet. Roast in oven until tender and 
lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, pat @rib-eye steaks{20%ounce}(dry) 
dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with plenty of @salt{}. Heat a large 
drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steaks and 
cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} 
and set aside to rest.

Wipe out pan used for steaks, then heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in it over 
medium heat. Add tomatoes, garlic, a pinch of chili flakes, and a @salt{pinch}. 
Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in 
@white wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, remaining honey, and ¼ cup water. Simmer until 
thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from heat and add @butter{1%tablespoon}; stir 
until melted. Season with @salt{}.

Slice steaks against the grain. Divide potatoes, carrots, and steaks between 
plates. Spoon chili tomato jam over steaks. Garnish with scallion greens.

> TIP: Sprinkle with more chili flakes, if desired, for extra heat.